          "date": "2014-09-24 03:21:22.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "DDN-77 osd: add OI file duplication functionality",
        "message": "DDN-77 osd: add OI file duplication functionality\n\n2.1 OI file may have consumed lots of space because it didn't release\nfree blocks, to shrink OI file, add OI file duplication functionality.\nThe duplicated OI file only contains valid records, so the size is\nmuch smaller than old one.\n\nDuring OI file duplication, if new files created, the newly added OI\nrecords may get missing, so it's suggested to umount lustre clients\nduring OI file duplication.\n\nAdd a sanity test 223 for this.\n\nSigned-off-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iaf0b4534fd7d7db870f7d85ca1f78c7e59ea184e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
